text.tspan: We are pulling VRef(ADC) down to 2.5v, this is more
that the 3.0v mentioned in Pico docs, a few extra mA
through R7, 200 rated at 100mW. Should be OK.
The Gnd symbol refers to Analog Ground not digital.
The 2n7000 with gate to drain is a 2v2 clamp, negligable
leakage of 2.6uA at 1.7v (compared with 32uA from a
string of forward biased diodes). At 2v, ie 200 degrees
Drain to Source on R ~ 8 ohms
The ratio of R0 to R1 affects the temp coeff but
they both affect the set current (ie 1mA).
Values here seem to suit 1n914 diode.
